          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Perfect! I've successfully identified and documented all the key C++ source files in Chromium's multi-process architecture. Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Summary of Chromium Multi-Process Architecture Files\n\n**1. RenderProcessHostImpl** (`content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h`)\n   - Browser-side representation of a renderer process\n   - Implements the RenderProcessHost interface\n   - Manages communication with renderer processes\n\n**2. BrowserMainLoop** (`content/browser/browser_main_loop.h`)\n   - Implements the main browser process event loop\n   - Manages browser initialization and shutdown\n   - Coordinates browser subsystems\n\n**3. RenderThreadImpl** (`content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h`)\n   - Main thread of a renderer process\n   - Implements the Renderer Mojo interface\n   - Hosts blink::WebView instances\n\n**4. ChildProcessLauncher** (`content/browser/child_process_launcher.h`)\n   - Asynchronously spawns child processes\n   - Abstracts platform-specific process creation\n   - Provides client callbacks for process readiness\n\n**5. Renderer Interface** (`content/common/renderer.mojom`)\n   - Mojo interface for browser-to-renderer communication\n   - Maintains FIFO ordering with legacy IPC messages\n   - Defines primordial channel-associated interface\n\nThe answer has been saved to `/workspace/answer.json` with complete file paths, symbols, and a detailed narrative explanation of how these components work together in Chromium's multi-process architecture.",
