        {
          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/browser/browser_main_loop.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/browser/child_process_launcher.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/common/renderer.mojom\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"RenderProcessHostImpl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/browser/browser_main_loop.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"BrowserMainLoop\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"RenderThreadImpl\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/browser/child_process_launcher.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ChildProcessLauncher\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"chromium/chromium\",\n      \"path\": \"content/common/renderer.mojom\",\n      \"symbol\": \"Renderer\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The Chromium multi-process architecture is defined across five key components:\\n\\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h, line 195): This class represents the browser-side of the browser-to-renderer communication channel. It implements the RenderProcessHost interface and is responsible for managing individual renderer processes. One RenderProcessHost exists per renderer process.\\n\\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (content/browser/browser_main_loop.h, line 106): This class implements the main browser process event loop stages. It manages the browser's main message loop and coordinates initialization and shutdown of browser subsystems.\\n\\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h, line 126): This class represents the main thread of a renderer process where blink::WebView instances live. It inherits from RenderThread and ChildThreadImpl, and implements the mojom::Renderer interface to receive messages from the browser.\\n\\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (content/browser/child_process_launcher.h, line 212): This class is responsible for asynchronously spawning and managing child processes (including renderer processes). It abstracts platform-specific process creation and provides a client interface for notification when the process is ready.\\n\\n5. **Renderer Interface** (content/common/renderer.mojom, line 49): This Mojo interface defines the primordial Channel-associated interface implemented by a render process. It is used for browser-to-renderer control messages that need to maintain FIFO ordering with legacy IPC messages.\\n\\nTogether, these components form the core of Chromium's multi-process architecture: RenderProcessHostImpl on the browser side communicates with RenderThreadImpl on the renderer side, with ChildProcessLauncher managing process creation, and the Renderer Mojo interface providing the IPC communication contract.\"\n}\n",
            "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json"
          },
